oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Patricia Jane Berg golfing in mid-swing at the Belle Meade Country Club.

Patricia Jane Berg (1918-2006) was a professional golfer and founding member of the Ladies Professional Golf Association. She won 60 professional events and had 15 major title wins. In 1946, she was the first champion of the U.S. Women's Open.
